name: turkey & quinoa meatloaf
instructions:
1. Preheat an oven to 350 degrees F.

2. Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. 

3. Dice onions, mince garlic, and add to hot oil.

4. Cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat to cool.

5. In a large bowl combine ground turkey, cooked quinoa, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, egg and cooled onion/garlic mixture. 

6. The mixture will be very moist. Shape into a loaf on a foil lined baking sheet. 

7. Bake in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the center and cooked through (165 degrees F), about 50 minutes.

8. Let the meatloaf cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.
